EmailTemplate.subject: Final Email - Family Profiles included
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hello Live Different Build Volunteers,
Your trip is happening so soon!!! Here are a few reminders to help you get ready for your trip.
IMPORTANT: FACEBOOK GROUP
You can add family and friends to this facebook group now! They can see photo updates from yourself as well as our staff on the ground.
Here is the link: https://www.facebook.com/groups/233520863786273/
ARRIVAL When you land in Puerto Plata, our staff will be wearing a Live Different t-shirt or holding a Live Different sign. Come find us and we'll take you back to Sosua by the Sea where you can unpack and meet the group. If there has been any flight changes, please email me right away and I can help you at any time.
If you are on the Westjet flight from Toronto to Puerto Plata on July 7, you will be flying with me. I will be at the gate an hour and a half early wearing a Live Different shirt. Send me a text if you can't find me. Here is my personal cell phone number just in case any last minute changes happen and you need to contact me. 905 746 0698
PASSPORTS Please bring 2 photocopies of your passport with you. One will be given to the resort staff upon check in, and the other is for you to keep on yourself. This is a precaution just in case your passport goes missing while travelling.
EMERGENCY CONTACTS If your family needs to contact you in case of emergency while in the Dominican Republic, these are the numbers to call:
Live Different Build Office:1-866-432-4464 (toll free) Brett: 1-829-675-3684 Sosua by the Sea: 809-571-3222
For general inquiries and non-urgent matters, please contact us via email at joy@livedifferent.com.
PHONE AND INTERNET ACCESS
Calling cards do not work in the DR. Some past volunteers have put international plans on their cell phones prior to leaving but you will need to contact your cell service provider to see if this is possible. There is wifi available for purchase at the resort. Costs for this are $2 for an hour, $5 for a day, $25 for the 10 days (USD). Some people like to bring their laptops as well, but keep in mind that Live Different is not responsible for lost or stolen items. There are safes available in the rooms for smaller valuable items, but they are not large enough to fit most laptops.
SPENDING MONEY/CURRENCY - It is best to bring cash in USD and Dominican pesos will be given as change when your purchase anything. - Please consider the following when deciding how much spending money to bring:
Your meals while traveling to and from your home to Puerto Plata $50 for any personal spending (for things like souvenirs or snacks) $30 USD we collect the resort staff tip and divide it evenly among each resort staff (housekeeping, kitchen staff, restaurant staff, front desk, etc.) $20 USD for a night out for dinner in a fun beach town with your team (a town called Caberete) $90 USD if you choose to participate in the day off excursion or you can hangout and enjoy the sun at the resort
PACKING LIST A packing list is attached for all who need it again. Don't forget to pack bug spray as there could be mosquito-borne illnesses.
FAMILY PROFILES
If you have questions, please let me know!
Joy Yu Program Administrator
